A palindrome is a word, phrase, or sequence of characters that reads the same forward and backward (ignoring spaces and capitalization).\", \"code\": \"def is_palindrome(s: str) -> bool:\\n    return s == s[::-1]\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert is_palindrome('racecar') == True\", \"assert is_palindrome('level') == False\", \"assert is_palindrome('A man, a plan, a canal, Panama') == True\"] }"
